    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-17T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-17T23:00:00-05:00" n="827"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d827">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/15268: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Kunming</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ringwalt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kunming</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-18T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >February 18, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 18—8:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Yunnan–Kweichow Pacification Headquarters has forwarded to Consulate General
                    through the special delegate a report on the Milo incident (telegram No. 6,
                    January 12, 5 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d827fn13">Not found in Department
                        files.</note>). Although not entirely satisfactory, headquarters Y force
                    agrees with this office that provided Embassy concurs no useful purpose would be
                    served in making further representations. Despatch follows.<note n="14"
                        xml:id="d827fn14">Despatch No. 34, February 18, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Chungking, repeated to Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ringwalt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
